<br>
At this point she asked everyone to go in and visit her....we were the last of the extended family to go and see her...we took the children to see her one afternoon..she said goodbye to them all..had a cuddle with the baby - asked DH (again) if all the kids were &quot;ok&quot; (read, not suffering from cerebral palsy..she never quite understood that it wasn't heriditary).  We all said goodbye to her..and as we walked out DH said to me &quot;that's the last time we will ever see her&quot;.<br>
