<br>
My best friend is currently the mother of 1 child, who was conceived while she had endometriosis, which as any woman will tell you is pretty close to a miracle itself, though it is still possible to conceive - though just barely.<br>
<br>
However, the miracle that I am talking about is that, 2 years ago, after attempting to treat her condition, she was told by multiple doctors that her only chance of conceiving another baby would be with the use of fertility drugs.  We (the church, pastors, etc.) have spent the last 2 years praying for her condition consistently.  Now, granted medical records are private - so, sorry, can't get you the medical records to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>prove</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> all of this - But her and I were going to the same doctor (RE &amp; Inf. Specialist)  Today she is 6 months pregnant with a baby boy, and I can tell you that this all came about the &quot;natural&quot; way. (Man, woman, no drugs, no doctors)<br>
<br>
Now this is a miracle to me, God intervened - and also, looks to me like the &quot;almighty science&quot; has failed on this one.  (3 doctors, all same diagnosis) Just interested to see how you write this one off.<br>
<br>
