<br>
This is a true story: When I was about 23 I sewed a sock monkey doll for a close friend of mine and I mailed it to her. When she got it, she called to thank me and said it cheered her up, she'd been feeling down, and by the way, she'd named the monkey &quot;Betty Badgley.&quot; I laughed and asked her why she named it that. She said the name had just popped into her head.<br>
<br>
A few weeks later, this friend got a new job in another city. She rented an apartment in a building that had a lot of older tennants. The day she moved in, she noticed the name of the previous tennant on her mailbox - &quot;E. Badgley.&quot; E was for Elizabeth, as in &quot;Betty.&quot;<br>
<br>
But what does it mean? Since I am a skeptic, I won't pretend to know that there IS a meaning, let alone what it might be. But this really happened and it seems too coincidental to just dismiss.<br>
<br>
