It is not impossible to get pregnant with endometriosis, and actually some women have no problem at all to get pregnant. It is also common for women diagnosed with &quot;fertility problems&quot; to get pregnant with no other help than &quot;taking charge of your fertility&quot; book. <br>
<br>
I have endometriosis. My reproductive organs are a mess, left ovary is completely encased in scar tissue, ligaments on left side are shortened and thickened and uterus is pulled entirely to the left. Right ovary is in slightly better condition but not much. Still, no doctor ever told me that it would be impossible for me to get pregnant (and due to endo problems, pain etc. I've seen many doctors in three different countries). <br>
Some actually told me that even though chances are extremely small, I should use bc if I don't want to get pregnant and also to reduce my chances of ectopic which is likely hiogher than chance of normal pregnancy with condition my ovaries and tubes are in. No doctor ever told me anything like &quot;impossible to get pregnant&quot;.<br>
I don't see any miracle there. <br>
<br>
A question for you who believe in faith healing - do you consider placebo effect a miracle? Do you think that people acting drunk while drinking soda they've been told is alcohol is a miracle?<br>
