<br>
Would the placebo effect include the times that others prayed for healing for someone who was not able to or wasn't aware that others were praying for them?  <br>
<br>
If you believe in faith healing, it would seem that you would also believe that the person receiving such healing would not necessariy have to be cognizant of others praying for them, as would be necessary to make the comparison to the placebo effect, where the recipient is aware that something is being done, but is tricked into thinking that he/she is receiving something that he/she is not.<br>
