<br>
do you mean a study on prayer were people are randomly asigned to groups prayed for and not prayed for? Several problems - people who sign up know that they may be prayed for so you can't completely exclude placebo effect. Whether the contributions of placebo effect would be the same in both groups depends on a number of factors (age, education, belief system etc.). Another problem is that if we assume that prayer works, how can you be sure that nobody is praying for people in control group? <br>
<br>
What about all those people who were prayed for and never recovered? Now you are probably going to say something about god's plan and god's mysterious ways... If he has a plan, what is the point of prayer? If he is omniscient and if he recovery of one person who is sick and suffering would not be against his plan why would you have to ask him to make that person better? Wouldn't loving god do so without anyone having to ask and not allow unnecessary suffering? Or do you think he is constantly changing his plans to accomodate for some of the prayers? <br>
<br>
Does he have some kind of a prayer lottery to decide which one will be fulfilled... Let's see - that Candice hairstyle will turn out fabulous for her firend's wedding? Fulfilled. That Jane&amp;Joe with 11 kids &amp; 12th on the way will get christmas toys for the kids from some charity - fulfilled. That Heather&amp;Fred finally conceive after rounds of clomid and several IVF attemps, praise be god and not doctors who helped them - fulfilled. Little boy dying from aids in Africa, little girl starving in Asia, baby girl left in a ditch to die in China - too bad, today's quota of prayers is fulfilled, or nobody faithfull enough prayed for them so they deserve to die, little bastards. Nice, isn't it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=55.topic&start=21&stop=28>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=55.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=55.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=55.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.threadControl?topicID=55.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligi